## SEO Implementation Notes (for you — remove before publishing)

1. **About pages rank differently than service pages** — they target brand-name searches ("NovaDesk reviews," "who is behind NovaDesk") and trust-building searches ("is [company] legitimate") rather than competitive service keywords. Keep this page honest and specific rather than keyword-stuffed; its job is conversion and trust, not primary traffic capture.

2. **Personalize every bracketed/italicized note** — generic founder-story language is one of the biggest trust-killers on About pages. Specific details (why you started, a real moment of frustration with the agency model, your actual educational background) make this page far more credible and memorable.

3. **Schema markup** — use `AboutPage` combined with a `Person` or `Organization` schema:
```html
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "AboutPage",
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "NovaDesk",
    "description": "A full-stack and AI development studio focused on full-stack web development, AI integration, and MVP development.",
    "url": "https://www.novadesk.site"
  }
}
</script>
```

4. **Internal linking**: Link to all service pages from the "What We Do" section, and link back to this About page from your homepage and footer — About pages often get linked from footers site-wide, which helps it accumulate authority.

5. **Accuracy over impressiveness**: The "Background & Approach" section is intentionally written to be adaptable — fill in real details, but don't overstate project status (e.g., don't call something "launched" if it's still in development). A client who asks a follow-up question and gets a mismatched answer damages trust far more than a modest, accurate claim would have in the first place.

6. **Word count**: ~1,150 words — appropriate depth for an About page without turning it into a full resume.